  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK, hands-- [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] well, to give you-- give you one the many examples, which is, again, it was unforgettable and very traumatic for me to even think about, is, at the height of that period, I do recall that one day my little brother was sent to the cellar to bring back some potatoes.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So he went to the cellar, and as I said, we were always, always thirsty.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were so thirsty that-- also, the hygiene was really poor.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "For instance, in our bedrooms, it was an upstairs bedroom, there was a pail for us to urinate through the night.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because it was always cold, so we couldn't go anywhere-- to the washrooms downstairs.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that pail in the morning was emptied, and fresh water was put in, but it was never scrubbed.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So after a while there was about, I would say, a good 1/2 inch of acid, uric acid, covering the inside of the-- of the pail, the bucket.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And yet, this is the-- from that bucket that we drank the water in the night because we were so thirsty.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So-- so because of the thirst my brother went-- little brother, who at that time that I'm talking about was six years old-- went to the cellar to pick up those potatoes.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He spotted a bottle of beer.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Belgians are big beer drinkers, they have these one liter bottles of beer.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I [? understand they're ?] brown bottles.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So he opened the bottle and took a sip.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Unfortunately, it didn't contain beer, it contained ammonia.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he let out a phenomenal scream because he completely burned his throat and everything in his esophagus.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So when we heard that scream, we all rushed down, including myself.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
